<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n01083h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n01" href="#n01083h">N01 (VI.B.10)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n01all.htm#n01083h"> 83(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ kosht (wood) ~</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[GIPSIES IN WINTER.]</font> It is part of his racial pride that makes the Romanichal reluctant to abandon the tawny tent in winter for a house. I have heard an old gipsy say that when lying convalescent in a hospital he &ldquo;was terribly afeared that the ceiling might come down on him.&rdquo; He was glad to get back to &ldquo;the old <i>tan</i>&rdquo; (tent) and put <mark><i>kosht</i></mark> (wood) on the <i>yog</i> (fire) and &ldquo;feel comfortable-like again.&rdquo; <small> <a name="DM28dec22" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#DM28dec22"><cite title="source">Daily Mail</cite></a> (28 December 1922) 6/5</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c05145j" href="c05all.htm#c05145j">VI.C.05:145(j)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
